From e04aa18116937b0f582a981d01dcadc6c667646e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 20:58:42 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 23/25] Remove the versioned handshake: presence of the entry
 points IS the protocol
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The version + capability-bit ceremony (unstable_externalRuntimeProtocol,
the reconciler's baked-in echo, errors 602/603 on skew or a missing
registry) guarded against a configuration our build process cannot
produce: react and the renderer always come from one build. Consumers
feature-detect the fork by the entry points' existence instead —
unstable_subscribeToExternalRuntime is undefined on stock React, which
is all the loud failure a binding needs.

Provider registration is now a plain push into the shared registry (a
no-op against a react package without one), the protocol/capabilities
fields are gone from both sides, and the three handshake tests and
error codes 602/603 go with them.
